1940;;King of the Royal Mounted;;American;;William Witney, John English;;Allan Lane;;adventure serial;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_of_the_Royal_Mounted_(serial);;In World War II, the Nazis require a special mineral, Compound X, discovered in Canada. Although intended to cure paralysis, the Nazis have discovered that it can be used in magnetic mines to destroy the British fleet and blockade America to prevent it assisting the Allies. The Mounties discover this plot and work to defeat and capture the Nazi spies sent to obtain the ore. Sgt King's father is killed in the line of duty, saving his son from death on a circular saw, and leaving him to carry on the fight against the enemy.<br><br>The plot was described as "pure and simple propaganda" by William Witney.[2]